A massive bonfire of paper documents and thick bureaucratic binders burning in a town square, flames reaching upward in warm oranges and golds, with the silhouettes of half-timbered German houses in the background at dusk. In the foreground, small green seedlings push through cracks in cobblestones, symbolizing new growth emerging from cleared ground. The scene has a vintage 1950s European poster style with muted earth tones, visible brushstroke textures, and slightly stylized proportions reminiscent of mid-century travel advertisements.
